{Eastbourne.} The population of Eastbourne, "The Suntrap of the South"is 79,000. Most of the building is residential with a good number of{hotels and guest {houses. }There is also an industrial area along Lottbridge Drove. An area of wet grassland is going to be turned into a big park with lakes, gardens and recreational facilities.
The main existing {parks}are Gildredge Park, Hampden Park and {Princes Park. Hampden Park has a pond and wildfowl, Princes Park has a boating lake. Near {Princes Park} is the {Leisure Pool.}
The largest hospital is the {District {General Hospital}in Kings Drive. The {Arndale Centre}and {Terminus Road}are the main shopping areas.
